---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../../components/Footer.astro';

const mediaBase = '/images/off-the-clock/cobra/exhaust';

const partSpecs = [
  { label: 'Part', value: 'Corsa Sport Axle-Back Exhaust' },
  { label: 'Part Number', value: '14311' },
  { label: 'Source', value: 'American Muscle' },
  { label: 'Ordered', value: 'June 25, 2022' },
  { label: 'Part Cost', value: '$981.99' },
  { label: 'Total (with tax)', value: '$1,044.81' },
  { label: 'Install', value: 'DIY — my garage' },
  { label: 'Install Time', value: '~2 hours' },
  { label: 'Difficulty', value: 'Beginner-friendly (bolt-on)' },
];

const comparisons = [
  {
    label: 'Cold Start',
    before: `${mediaBase}/old-start-up.mp4`,
    after: `${mediaBase}/new-start-up.mp4`,
    caption: 'The initial bark and idle. Listen to how the V8 note fills in after the Corsa install.',
  },
  {
    label: 'Quick Rev',
    before: `${mediaBase}/old-quick-rev.mp4`,
    after: `${mediaBase}/new-quick-rev.mp4`,
    caption: 'A punch of the throttle. This is where the supercharger whine dominated the stock exhaust — and where the Corsa lets the V8 answer back.',
  },
  {
    label: 'Slow Build',
    before: `${mediaBase}/old-slow-rev.mp4`,
    after: `${mediaBase}/new-slow-rev.mp4`,
    caption: 'Gradual RPM climb. For the car people who want to really hear how the balance shifts across the rev range.',
  },
];

const photos = [
  { src: `${mediaBase}/before-rear-stock-tips.jpg`, alt: 'Rear view with stock exhaust tips — selective color highlighting the red stripe', blurPlate: true },
  { src: `${mediaBase}/before-rear-wide.jpg`, alt: 'Wider rear shot in the garage with stock exhaust tips', blurPlate: true },
  { src: `${mediaBase}/after-rear-corsa-tips.jpg`, alt: 'Rear view with Corsa tips installed' },
  { src: `${mediaBase}/after-tip-closeup-left.jpg`, alt: 'Close-up of installed Corsa tip — driver side' },
  { src: `${mediaBase}/after-tip-closeup-right.jpg`, alt: 'Close-up of installed Corsa tip — passenger side' },
  { src: `${mediaBase}/after-tip-closeup-angle.jpg`, alt: 'Corsa tip and bumper cutout from a different angle' },
  { src: `${mediaBase}/corsa-muffler-detail.jpg`, alt: 'Corsa muffler assembly close-up showing weld quality' },
  { src: `${mediaBase}/corsa-brand-tip.jpg`, alt: 'Corsa Performance branding etched into the polished tip' },
];
---

<BaseLayout title="Corsa Sport Exhaust — 2008 Shelby GT500 — Steve Minster">
  <Header />

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="section-dark pt-32 pb-16">
    <div class="max-w-wide mx-auto px-6">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6">
        <a href="/off-the-clock" class="hover:text-lime transition-colors">Off the Clock</a>
        <span class="mx-2">/</span>
        <a href="/off-the-clock/cobra" class="hover:text-lime transition-colors">2008 Shelby GT500</a>
        <span class="mx-2">/</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Exhaust</span>
      </nav>
      <p class="font-display text-label uppercase tracking-widest text-lime mb-3">The Build Log</p>
      <h1 class="font-display text-hero mb-6" style="color: #475569;">
        Finding the Growl.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-electric text-lg max-w-2xl">
        The supercharger was winning. Time to let the V8 fight back.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Story -->
  <section class="section-light py-16">
    <div class="max-w-wide mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-5 gap-12">
        <!-- Prose (wider) -->
        <div class="lg:col-span-3 reveal">
          <!-- The Problem -->
          <div class="mb-10">
            <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-h2 text-navy mb-4">The Problem</h2>
            <div class="space-y-5 text-slate text-body">
              <p>
                The 2008 GT500's Eaton supercharger is not a subtle piece of machinery. At idle, you hear it. Under throttle, it screams. And somewhere underneath all that forced-induction whine is a 5.4-liter V8 that's supposed to sound like a muscle car.
              </p>
              <p>
                With the stock exhaust, the blower was dominating the conversation. The V8 rumble was buried — you could hear it, but it wasn't asserting itself. Zeus sounded fast. I wanted him to sound <em>angry</em>.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- The Choice -->
          <div class="mb-10">
            <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-h2 text-navy mb-4">The Choice</h2>
            <div class="space-y-5 text-slate text-body">
              <p>
                I went with the <strong>Corsa Sport Axle-Back Exhaust</strong> (Part #14311) from American Muscle. Corsa's "Sport" sound level — not the "Xtreme" — because I wasn't trying to set off car alarms. The goal was to rebalance the sound profile: bring the V8 growl forward without losing the supercharger character entirely.
              </p>
              <p>
                The system uses Corsa's patented RSC (Reflective Sound Cancellation) technology, which is a fancy way of saying they engineered the drone out of it. Aggressive under acceleration, quiet at cruise. That mattered — Zeus is still a convertible I drive on the highway.
              </p>
              <div class="mt-6">
                <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-h3 text-navy mb-3">The specs:</h3>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-slate">
                  <li>2.5" axle-back, dual rear exit</li>
                  <li>4.0" polished Pro-Series stainless steel tips</li>
                  <li>304 stainless steel construction</li>
                  <li>Bolt-on install — no cutting, no welding</li>
                  <li>Made in Berea, Ohio</li>
                  <li>~7 lbs lighter than stock</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- The Install -->
          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-h2 text-navy mb-4">The Install</h2>
            <div class="space-y-5 text-slate text-body">
              <p>
                This is about as DIY-friendly as a mod gets. Jack up the car, unbolt the stock axle-back, bolt on the Corsa. No cutting, no welding, no trips to the shop. I did it on a Saturday afternoon in my garage and was done before the afternoon got hot.
              </p>
              <p>
                If you can operate a socket wrench and a jack stand, you can do this install. The Corsa system comes with all the hardware and a full-color instruction guide. The hardest part was wrestling the stock mufflers out from under the car — they're heavier than you'd expect.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Part Detail Card (sidebar) -->
        <div class="lg:col-span-2 reveal">
          <div class="card lg:sticky lg:top-24">
            <div class="h-1" style="background-color: #97D700;"></div>
            <div class="p-6">
              <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-h3 text-navy mb-4">Part Details</h3>
              <dl class="space-y-3">
                {partSpecs.map((spec) => (
                  <div class="flex flex-col">
                    <dt class="text-xs font-display uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-400">{spec.label}</dt>
                    <dd class="text-slate font-medium text-sm">{spec.value}</dd>
                  </div>
                ))}
              </dl>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Hear the Difference -->
  <section class="section-dark py-16">
    <div class="max-w-wide mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="reveal mb-12">
        <p class="font-display text-label uppercase tracking-widest text-lime mb-3">Before &amp; After</p>
        <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-h2 text-white mb-4">Hear the Difference</h2>
        <p class="text-electric text-body max-w-3xl">
          Three clips, three approaches — startup, quick rev, and slow rev. Same phone, same position in the garage. Listen for the V8 growl pushing through after the swap.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-16">
        {comparisons.map((comp, i) => (
          <div class="reveal" style={`transition-delay: ${i * 0.1}s`}>
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-h3 text-white mb-2">{comp.label}</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400 text-small mb-6">{comp.caption}</p>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <!-- Before -->
              <div>
                <span class="inline-block px-3 py-1 text-xs font-display uppercase tracking-wider bg-gray-700 text-gray-300 rounded-full mb-3">Before — Stock</span>
                <video controls preload="metadata" class="w-full aspect-square rounded-lg bg-black">
                  <source src={comp.before} type="video/mp4" />
                </video>
              </div>
              <!-- After -->
              <div>
                <span class="inline-block px-3 py-1 text-xs font-display uppercase tracking-wider bg-lime/20 text-lime rounded-full mb-3">After — Corsa</span>
                <video controls preload="metadata" class="w-full aspect-square rounded-lg bg-black">
                  <source src={comp.after} type="video/mp4" />
                </video>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <!-- Unboxing -->
      <div class="mt-16 reveal">
        <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-h3 text-white mb-2">The Unboxing</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-small mb-6">What shows up when you order a Corsa axle-back from American Muscle.</p>
        <div class="max-w-lg">
          <video controls preload="metadata" class="w-full aspect-square rounded-lg bg-black">
            <source src={`${mediaBase}/unboxing.mp4`} type="video/mp4" />
          </video>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Photo Gallery -->
  <section class="section-light py-16">
    <div class="max-w-wide mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="reveal mb-10">
        <p class="font-display text-label uppercase tracking-widest text-lime mb-3">Gallery</p>
        <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-h2 text-navy mb-4">The Details</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
        {photos.map((photo, i) => (
          <div class="reveal overflow-hidden rounded-lg" style={`transition-delay: ${i * 0.06}s`}>
            <img
              src={photo.src}
              alt={photo.alt}
              loading="lazy"
              class="w-full aspect-square object-cover hover:scale-105 transition-transform duration-500"
            />
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DIY or Pro? + What's Next -->
  <section class="section-dark py-16">
    <div class="max-w-wide mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl reveal">
        <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-h2 text-white mb-4">DIY or Pro?</h2>
        <div class="space-y-5 text-electric text-body">
          <p>
            <strong class="text-lime">Verdict: DIY.</strong> This was a wrench-in-hand Saturday afternoon project. The Corsa axle-back is a true bolt-on — no fabrication, no welding, no special tools beyond what's in most garage toolboxes. If you're on the fence about doing exhaust work yourself, an axle-back swap is the right place to start.
          </p>
          <p>
            I'll be honest about when a mod is over my head. This one wasn't. Save the shop bill for the stuff that actually needs a lift and a pro.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="max-w-3xl mt-16 reveal">
        <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-h2 text-slate mb-4">What's Next</h2>
        <div class="space-y-5 text-electric text-body mb-8">
          <p>
            The exhaust gave Zeus his voice. But there's more on the list — a front bumper replacement to clean up some road rash, and a radio upgrade to bring the cabin into the current decade. Those stories are coming.
          </p>
        </div>
        <a href="/off-the-clock/cobra" class="btn-secondary text-sm">← Back to the Cobra</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
